records.addlTxt: To Seal Victim/Witness Identification Key, signed by Judge Michael O. Bohren on November 3, 2022.

9:29 AM Defendant Emanuel D Tubbins in court, in custody.  Attorney Anna M Kees in court for Emanuel D Tubbins.  Prosecuting attorney Jack A. Pitzo in court for the State of Wisconsin. Attorney Kees previously filed a motion to dismiss Count 1 and makes arguments in support of her motion. Attorney Pitzo makes arguments in support of the State's objection to the motion to dismiss Count 1. For reasons stated on the record, the Court will deny the motion to dismiss Count 1. After Attorney Kees has further discussions with the defendant, he wishes to proceed with a preliminary hearing. The Court calls all three co-defendant cases simultaneously at 9:42 AM. City of Waukesha Police Department Detective Jessica Behrendt sworn in and testifies on direct by Attorney Pitzo. Cross examination by Attorney Kees. Redirect by Attorney Pitzo. State rests. State moves for bind over with argument. Attorney Kees objects to bind over without argument. Court finds probable cause to believe that a felony was committed and binds the defendant over for trial. Waive reading of Information. NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED. Bail remains as fixed.
Hearing scheduled for January 25, 2023 at 09:30 am.

Defendant waives his/her right to a Preliminary Hearing.
